## 5. WHAT IS DONE WELL

### ✅ Architecture Integrity
- All 5 physics-derived components are implemented as **independent, clean PyTorch modules** — not hacked into a monolithic model
- Each component has a module-level docstring explaining which constraint it implements
- The `MANTA.forward()` method is clearly annotated with constraint tags (`# Constraint 1:`, `# Constraint 5:`) at every step
- No unexplained CNN layers — every convolutional layer has a comment explaining its physical purpose

### ✅ Palindromic Convolution (Constraint 4)
- `PalindromicConv1d` is mathematically correct: half-kernel parameterization with mirror concatenation
- Test `test_palindromic_symmetry` verifies `kernel == flip(kernel)` with tight tolerance
- The SymmetricTransitEncoder correctly stacks palindromic layers with EllipticMish — no ReLU leaks
- Kernel sizes (9, 7, 5) are odd as required and configurable

### ✅ Parallel Frequency Branches (Constraint 5 — Architecture)
- Three genuinely parallel branches: `GranulationBranch`, `AsteroseismologyBranch`, `StarspotBranch`
- Kernel sizes are physically motivated and match timescale hierarchy (15→dilated for granulation, 5/3 for astero, 21/11 for starspot)
- Branches are concatenated, not sequential — true parallelism
- Branch feature maps are cached for visualization (`get_feature_maps()`)

### ✅ Data Pipeline Quality
- Robust NaN handling with configurable strategies (`hybrid`, `interpolate`, `mask`)
- Star-level train/val/test splitting prevents leakage (`split_dataset` groups by Kepler ID)
- Phase folding and binning are correct with median binning
- Transit injection uses batman with proper Mandel-Agol model and varied limb-darkening coefficients

### ✅ Training Infrastructure
- Kaggle-aware emergency checkpointing with session time estimation
- Full state saving (model + optimizer + scheduler + metrics + config)
- Focal BCE loss with physically motivated justification
- Gradient clipping for attention stability
- Early stopping on validation AUC-ROC

### ✅ Config System
- Strongly typed dataclass configuration with validation
- Physical constants are named and documented (`KEPLER_LONG_CADENCE_MINUTES`)
- Config validation catches physically impossible values (e.g., `rp_rs_max > 0.2`)

### ✅ Code Quality
- Consistent type annotations throughout
- NumPy-style docstrings on every public method with parameter/return documentation
- Physically meaningful variable names (`limb_darkening_bias`, `palindromic_kernel`, `rotation_freq`)
- Proper logging at INFO/DEBUG levels

### ✅ Testing Foundation
- Output bounds test (Constraint 3): verifies all outputs in `[1e-6, 1-1e-6]`
- Gradient flow test: verifies all parameters receive gradients
- Data pipeline tests: NaN handling, phase fold centering, reconstruction error
- Tests use synthetic data — no network calls

